Zack - email please - ckmorris95@....  I got a chip from Sum - but
I currently have the 470 so I don&#39;t need it.

k



  _____  

From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
Frank Ratka
Sent: Friday, January 04, 2008 8:25 AM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Re: Any way to speed up the scanning on the 12-469?-A
couple more questions



Mine has already been installed. Sorry!

Frank R.

----- Original Message ----
From: Zack Widup &lt;w9sz@...&gt;
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Friday, January 4, 2008 7:18:42 AM
Subject: RE: [EVP-ITC] Re: Any way to speed up the scanning on the 12-469?-A
couple more questions


Yes, if they&#39;re not code-protected. Anyone have one they&#39;d like to 
volunteer?

Zack

On Fri, 4 Jan 2008, Frank Sumption wrote:

&gt;
&gt; What about copying it from one of the chips?
&gt;
&gt; Frank-S
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .comFrom &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.comFrom&gt; :
w9sz@prairienet. orgDate &lt;mailto:w9sz%40prairienet.orgDate&gt; : Thu, 3 Jan
2008 22:57:07 -0600Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Re: Any way to speed up the
scanning on the 12-469?-A couple more questions
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; The chip is a microcontroller. It needs a program called &quot;firmware&quot; put
into it before it will do anything useful. The chips have a program memory
which comes blank when you buy them.The &quot;code&quot; is the representation of what
is called machine language that tells the various parts of the
microcontroller what to do. In this case, I imagine it increases a voltage
with a certain pattern and then drops it down to zero, starting over again
and repeating at a certain rate. This would produce a repetitive sweep of
the radio at a certain rate when the microcontroller is hooked up to the
radio correctly.It wouldn&#39;t be difficult for me to write my own program to
do this with a PIC microcontroller, but if someone else has already done it,
why bother?If I can&#39;t get my hands on the machine code, I&#39;ll write some
myself.ZackOn Fri, 4 Jan 2008, mllejade wrote:&gt; Frank, please let me know if
you should, for whatever reason, decide&gt; to sell that chip (to control the
scan rate of the &#39;469). I&#39;d like&gt; to purchase it from you, if possible.&gt;&gt;
Thanks,&gt;&gt; Sharon&gt;&gt; P.S. I&#39;ve read the follow-ups to my initial question and
being a&gt; layman at modifying electric apparatuses, what do you all mean by&gt;
code? Does one need the code and the chip in order to speed up the&gt; scanning
on a hacked &#39;469; or can one do it with simply a code, or&gt; the chip,
alone?&gt;&gt;&gt; --- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&gt;
, Frank Sumption &lt;franks-boxes@ ...&gt;&gt; wrote:&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Yeah, the guy that first
made the hack was giving away a chip to&gt; control the scan rate. I don&#39;t know
if it&#39;s still available. I have&gt; one of the chips, and no &#39;469.&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
Frank-S&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt; To: EVP-ITC@...: leongbabe@.. .: Thu, 3 Jan 2008 16:37:00&gt;
+0000Subject: [EVP-ITC] Any way to speed up the scanning on the 12-&gt;
469?&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; I&#39;m still relatively new to building boxes and would like to
know&gt; if it&#39;s possible to speed up the scanning a bit on a hacked RS 12-&gt;
469. Thanks,Sharon --- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com
&lt;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&gt; , Frank Sumption&gt; &lt;franks-boxes@ &gt;
wrote:&gt;&gt; &gt; Thanks for listening. Yeah, that&#39;s the&gt; problem with noise
reduction methods, they tend to take out voices. I&gt; think if I used the
muffled sound consistently they would talk&gt; through it though, the goal
being to get higher level voices, and&gt; audio. The clarifier is just a low
pass filter that can be adjusted--&gt; just an idea.&gt; I have some female guides
that speak sometimes, and&gt; there&#39;s the seven sisters that come though
sometimes, but I don&#39;t&gt; know much about that. &gt; &gt; Frank-S&gt; &gt; &gt; To: EVP-ITC@:
debbie@: Wed, 2&gt; Jan 2008 10:33:33 -0700Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] The &#39;470
mod?&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;&gt; Frank, Thanks for the extra instructions, it doesn&#39;t sound
too&gt; difficult for me so I&#39;ll give it a shot. &gt; &gt; By the way, I did listen&gt;
to your tone control clip. Since I&#39;m new to this my comments are&gt; probably
not &quot;worth&quot; much at this point. I thought the entire clip&gt; itself was a lot
smoother and clearer than most I&#39;ve heard so far&gt; from various sources (the
mixed station sounds are in smaller pieces&gt; so for someone like me it would
be easier to pick out the EVPs as&gt; opposed to entire words from radio
announcers). The short piece about&gt; 2/3 of the way through, where I&#39;m
guessing you used a clarifier,&gt; sounded muffled to me, which makes me think
it would also muffle the&gt; EVPs. Definitely easier on the ears but for
someone inexperienced&gt; (and I seem to be the only one here!) it seems it
would be harder to&gt; pick out the real words too.&gt; &gt; By the way, in listening
to the&gt; deluge of clips uploaded last night, I can&#39;t help but notice that
the&gt; voices are all men. Just curious -- is that always the case?&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _&gt; &gt; Debbie Tejada&gt; &gt; &quot;Once you can accept&gt; the
universe as matter expanding into nothing that is something,&gt; wearing
stripes with plaid comes easy. &quot; ~Albert Einstein&gt; &gt; On Jan&gt; 2, 2008, at
10:22 AM, Frank Sumption wrote:&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; I have&gt; the &#39;470, but I don&#39;t
know if it&#39;s the older one or not. I was able&gt; to modify it, but it was
somewhat different than in the video&gt; instruction, there was more than one
green wire. You have to lift the&gt; top board so you can see the wire
connections on the other board,&gt; they are labeled, and you can tell what
wire to cut/unsolder. (mute&gt; wire). Frank-S&gt; &gt; Share life as it happens with
the new Windows Live.&gt; Share now! &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;&gt; ____________ _________
_________ _________ _________ _________ _&gt; Get the&gt; power of Windows + Web
